post_text:
Be on the lookout! Our 2020 Fall Newsletter is heading out to mailboxes ü•≥ Ms Martha, Ms Michelle, and Ms Jaime have been working together to figure out ways to accommodate our families. Things look different this year but we will be in contact with families soon!
Since we cannot have visitors in the library our Story Time will be the third Thursday of every month but virtual to start. Our playgroups will be virtual the first Thursday of the month; watch our Facebook page for a poll to help us decide on a time to provide this! Thank you all and we look forward to seeing you!

post_text:
We are still scheduling for our screenings to fill our fall preschool and pre-K programs! We currently have openings for screening on June 15. It is a free service, and required to attend our preschool and pre-K through the school. We have a team of educators ready and will be following CDC guidelines on screening day! Please call Michelle Dalinghaus at 712-269-4046 to schedule!

Students testing for preschool must have birthdays prior to August 1, 2017. Pre-K students must have birthdays prior to August 1, 2016. Families must live in the Lathrop school district.

I would like to wish all our Moms a Happy Mother‚Äôs Day! I read something in the paper this week I love.....
At 3 years ‚ÄúMommy I love you!, At 10 years ‚ÄúMom, whatever‚Äù At 16 years ‚ÄúMom, you‚Äôre so annoying.‚Äù At 18 years ‚ÄúI‚Äôm leaving this house!‚Äù At 25 years ‚ÄúMom, you are right‚Äù At 50 years ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt want to lose my mom.‚Äù At 70 years ‚ÄúI would give up everything to have my mom here with me!‚Äù
Enjoy your day with your family!

shared_text:
Kendra Bryant Gagnon updated her status.
January 5, 2017 at 4:03 PM ¬∑

I'm looking for some babies and children to participate in some gross motor assessment labs in the Pediatric PT course I teach at Rockhurst University this spring. I need babies age 0-12 months for the ‚ÄúBaby Lab‚Äù on 2/8 and children age 1-6 years for the ‚ÄúChild lab‚Äù on 2/22. Children and families will need to be there from 8:30-11:30. Two groups of DPT students will assess the child‚Äôs gross motor skills. The tests they will be performing are play-based and will involve lots of observation, interaction, and asking questions of parents/caregivers. Students will be looking at movement skills such as rolling, crawling, walking, running, jumping, and playing ball. Families usually find it interesting and the kids have a lot of fun! Children of ALL abilities are welcome. Message me if interested!
